text: Not too bad. Boss is friendly. Prata freshly made, wish the curry could be spicier

I live right across and this shop is new so i wanted to try and there staff so mean sia
I got coin prata and waiting so long i was paitient then when it was payment i was in a queue and a chinese man asked me hey can i cut queue and i respectfylly said no EVEN AFTER HEARING THIS CONVERSATION THEY LET HIM PAY FIRST BEFORE ME WHAT KIND OF SERVICE IS THIS!!

Thosai and dal gravy were fine but nothing extraordinary. Had to ask for bread to go with mutton soup. Unfortunately the mutton soup was less than satisfactory,  as it was mostly all soup with a few miserable small pieces of meat. Can improve on process of order and pay management as it was unruly with more customers.
